  "prompt": "How did people communicate in the pre-internet era?",
  "response": "Before the internet, people used various methods to communicate:\n\n1. Telephone\n- Landline phones\n- Public payphones\n- Long-distance and international calling\n\n2. Mail\n- Postal mail/letters\n- Postcards\n- Telegrams\n- Packages\n\n3. Face-to-face communication\n- In-person conversations\n- Meetings\n- Family gatherings\n\n4. Print media\n- Newspapers\n- Magazines\n- Newsletters\n- Bulletins\n\n5. Other communication methods\n- Fax machines\n- Telex\n- Ham radio\n- Intercom systems\n- Message boards\n\n6. Social communication\n- Writing letters\n- Sending postcards\n- Making phone calls\n- Visiting in person\n- Community gatherings\n\n7. Professional communication\n- Business letters\n- Memos\n- Phone calls\n- Conferences\n- In-person meetings\n\nEach method had its own advantages and limitations, but people generally relied on slower, more personal forms of communication compared to today's digital methods.",
